00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Namaste everyone, today we will study the profound teachings of Krishna

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:12,000
from the Bhagavad Gita chapter two about dharma and the eternal soul

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Krishna tells Arjuna in verse two forty seven, karmany eva adhikaram te

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:25,000
ma phaleshu kadachana, you have the right to perform actions but never

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
to the fruits of action, this is the essence of nishkama karma

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:37,000
The concept of ahimsa, non-violence, is fundamental in yoga philosophy

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:44,000
When we practice pranayama and meditation, we purify the chitta

8
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The ultimate goal is moksha, liberation from the cycle of samsara

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:57,000
As taught in the Upanishads, tat tvam asi, thou art that

10
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Through sadhana and devotion to guru, we realize our true nature as Atman